members.doc: Operator that indicates a dependency on another subject being allowed to perform something.

members.doc: The attribute which should be compared. The attribute will be first evaluated to a value, and then compared the other side (attribute/value)

members.doc: The value to compare to. If the two parties are equal - we will return true.

members.name: attrName
members.doc: The attribute which should be compared. The attribute will be first evaluated to a value, and then compared the regex values provided.

members.doc: The regex values which the attribute value should be evaluated on. If the attribute value matches at least one of the regular expressions provided - we will return true

members.doc: The spec to conduct the experiment on.

members.doc: The value to use if the experiment could not be conducted

members.doc: The expected value of the experiment conduction. If it matches the actual value - true will be returned. Otherwise - false.

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ACCOUNT
  • USER
  • USER_GROUP
  • MEMBER_GROUP
  • VISITOR_GROUP
  • EXTERNAL_APP

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_CTX
  • ORG_CTX
  • ACCOUNT_CTX

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_SIMPLE_OP
  • EQUAL

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_JOIN_OP
  • OR
  • AND

Invite status stating whether the invite was accepted, waiting to be accepted, deleted etc.. Possible values are:
  • Pending
  • Used
  • Deleted
  • Declined
  • Expired

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_RESOURCE_TYPE
  • SITE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_CONDITION_TYPE
  • FOLDER

Possible values are:
  • UNDEF_PEOPLE_TYPE
  • CONTRIBUTOR
  • TEAM_MEMBER

Possible values are:
  • Visible - the role should be visible to the caller
  • Disabled_Dependency - the role should be disabled for the caller, because it contains permissions the caller wasn't granted on the call context (site/account)
  • Disabled_Capability - the role should be disabled for the caller, because the role's capability is disabled for the caller

Possible values are:
  • UNINITIALIZED
  • EDITORX
  • BLOCKS

Possible values are:
  • NoRestriction
  • Site
  • Account

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_STATUS
  • PREDEFINED
  • CUSTOM
  • INLINE_CUSTOM

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_EFFECT
  • ALLOW
  • DENY

Possible values are:
  • Undefined
  • Roles - How many team members with each role
  • InviteStatus - How many team members by invite status
  • Users - How many team members in total in the account

Possible values are:
  • None
  • SITE
  • ACCOUNT

Possible values are:
  • ALL
  • SITE_LEVEL
  • ACCOUNT_LEVEL

Possible values are:
  • UninitializedDirection
  • ASC
  • DESC

Possible values are:
  • Undefined
  • Name
  • JoinedAt

Possible values are:
  • VISIBLE - The scope should be visible to the caller
  • BLOCKED_BY_CAPABILITY - The scope shouldn't be visible for the caller, because the capability that blocks it is turned on for the caller
